	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Hi,<br />
<br />
I read the Blizzard FAQ on their PvP, but it didn't really tell me much.  I am looking for some finer details.<br />
<br />
I know that there are red and blue servers, but not sure the real difference.<br />
<br />
I am pretty sure there is some PvP on a blue server, but is it totally consensual or can I run to the undead area and just start killing other players?  <br />
<br />
On a red server, if I am playing a Night Elf, do I have to worry about other Night Elves hunting me?<br />
<br />
I have read that there is not much of a penalty for PvP death, but what penalty is there?<br />
<br />
So, basically, I guess I am looking for an overall view of the PvP system.<br />
<br />
Thanks</p>
	
	
	
