	<!-- message -->
	<p>From what I've read on the PvP servers, anyone can attack anyone, though I seem to remember something about how in Alliance zones Horde are unable to initiate PvP and in Horde zones Alliance are unable to initiate PvP but in any non controlled zone PvP can be initiated by either side.<br />
<br />
On the PvE servers, I think you can choose to enter PvP state for yourself only, however if you kill a PvP flagged Npc you become PvP enabled for 5 minutes (I think thats correct time) or if you heal or buff anyone with a PvP flag active you also become PvP active for 5 minutes.<br />
<br />
They are attempting to have no downside to PvP just rewards in various forms including boosting your faction with your side to reduce costs get extra quests. Also they have mentioned the possiblity of rewarding the top PvP'ers further.<br />
<br />
One thing that could be seen as a detriment is that Horde and Alliance have seperate GY's and therefore if you die in the middle of your opposite factions area you will likely end up with a long CR.</p>
	
	
	
