	<!-- message -->
	<p>PVP server - any horde can attack any alliance, and vice versa. People of the same side cannot attack each other unless it is via a consentual duel. This keeps the focus on faction vs faction<br />
<br />
I didn't play too long on non-pvp server but this is my understanding.<br />
<br />
Non PVP server - You can flag yourself for pvp, which is your way of giving consent for pvp competition. If you flag yourself for pvp or if you attack someone who is flagged for pvp, then you are able to be attacked as well. Attacking NPCs of the opposite faction (any NPC that you can attack) will flag you for PvP, even if you didn't attack a Player Character. You can also be swarmed by guards of any opposing faction if your reputation is bad enough with them (check character sheet)</p>
	
	
	
	
	
