	<!-- message -->
	<p>You type in /pvp to turn on pvp mode on a carebear server.<br />
It lasts for about 5 mins.<br />
A little symbol appears on your character window on the top left side.<br />
If you click on any guard as your target, you'll see the same symbol up (indicating they are constantly set up for PvP).<br />
So basicly, if anyone decides it's cool to try and slaughter the opposing side's guards and shopkeepers, the people of that home town and jump them and defend their home town, regardless of the server type.<br />
I think I'll actually try playing on a PvP server this time around with WoW.</p>
	
	
	
