	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>On the PVP servers you have 3 kinds of territories:<br />
<br />
1. Your own faction territory, Alliance territory or Horde Territory, depending which side you are on you cannot be attacked by the other faction UNLESS you attack them first.  These territories are mostly the newbie territories. I noticed on Alliance side you can easily level up to 20 without leaving Alliance territory.<br />
<br />
This is how I encountered it anyway, I had 5 trolls surrounding me in Auberdine and all I did was /dance and /laugh because they couldn't attack me (I'm on test 4 ET pvp).  <br />
<br />
<br />
2. Contested territory:  Horde can attack Alliance, Alliance can attack Horde.<br />
<br />
3. Opposite faction territory: As an Alliance you cannot attack a Horde char when you are in Horde Territory.  <br />
I am not sure what happened to you there Walruss if you didn't attack him first.<br />
<br />
EDIT: regarding the durability loss during PVP, I also thought they removed that.</p>
	
	
	
