	<p>I had my first PvP experience yesterday.  I play a lvl 14 troll warrior on Test 38 (mountain zone, pvp).<br />
<br />
From what I've seen.  If an Alliance player wants to come to Horde lands and dodge NPC guards, etc., they can.  In fact they can hang out unmolested in the newbie area and they can't kill anyone unless they are attacked first.  <br />
<br />
What happened was, a level 18 dwarf hunter went to the troll/orc newbie zone and /duel'd the newbies and then promptly waxed them when they accepted.  We all ran there, and if we engaged him, then the fight was on.  Otherwise you sit and stare at each other.  He couldn't attack until he was attacked.<br />
<br />
So we all ran to defend our town, I tanked his pet while my wife kept me healed.  The pet itself was a tough fight.  He was shooting at some other folks and then came to fight me when he saw his pet going down.  We had a mob that finally chased him down and killed him.  Next time, he came back with a 19 pallie.  I thought the 19 said '14" so I attacked the pallie and got promptly slaughtered by him after he stunned me.<br />
<br />
It was fun though, but I doubt I'll pvp when it goes live.  I am on this server just for the low population lol.<br />
<br />
Mach<br />
(Bitaee - 14 troll warrior, Test 38)</p>
	
	
	
