<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Nuttasaurus</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Disciple<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Jul 2002<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Yeah sorry guys there is some misinformation about PVP in this thread so far, but Kykha got it heading in the right direction.<br />
<br />
Each zone has a name and color code for faction:<br />
friendly/green.  contested/yellow.  hostile/red.<br />
<br />
While in a green zone you are safe and cannot be attacked first.  If you attack an enemy here you will now be flagged for PVP however.<br />
<br />
Yellow/contested all enemies should appear red and that means fair game/open combat for all opposing factions.<br />
<br />
Red/Hostile you cannot attack the enemy - basically you are on their turf and the idea with this is these zones are primarily nebie zones so your lvl 60 can't go freely gank lvl 5s.  However if they attack you then they are PVP flagged and fair game.<br />
<br />
There is no PVP among your own faction unless you /duel or go to the arena which is open combat for all.<br />
<br />
Even if you aren't into PVP I highly recommend at least duelling some =)</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=12939" target="_blank">Qatol</a><br />
65 Seasons of Scaly Shaman Hijinks<br />
