<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>snapdragn</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Brute in a Suit<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Apr 2002<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>For the "Simple" explanation:<br />
<br />
<b>PvP is exactly the same on all servers</b>.  You can ONLY fight members of the opposite team.  You can ONLY PvP when both you and your opponent are PvP flagged. <br />
<br />
Now heres the gotcha:<br />
<br />
<b>There are two sets of rules that will flag you for PvP, one for each server type.</b><br />
<br />
On a <font color="blue">NON-PvP</font>  server, you only get flagged for PvP if you do the following:<br />
<br />
a)  attacking an NPC of the opposing faction<br />
b)  attacking a player who attacked an NPC<br />
c)  aiding a player engaged in PvP. <br />
d)  typing /pvp<br />
<br />
On a <font color="red">PvP </font>  server, you get flagged for PvP if you do the following:<br />
<br />
a) attacking an NPC of the opposing faction<br />
b) attacking another player<br />
c) aiding a player engaged in PvP.<br />
d) entering or being in an enemy territory<br />
e) entering or being in a contested territory<br />
<br />
Basically, any zone you want to quest/xp in past lvl 20 is a contested territory (on PvP servers).  Any newbie zone or city zone is a friendly/enemy territory (on PvP servers). <br />
<br />
So on PvP servers, you can be attacked in most zones where you will be adventuring, but your own cities and newb areas are safe.  Instanced zones are also safe, obviously.<br />
<br />
Examples:<br />
<br />
Orc and human groups come across each other in a lvl 40 zone. <br />
PvP server:  they can attack each other on sight.<br />
nonPvP:  they can only attack each other if somebody from both sides 'turns on' their pvp flag (by typing /pvp).  <br />
<br />
Orc and human group come across each other in the human newb land.<br />
PvP server:  Orcs can't do anything, Humans can attack on sight.<br />
nonPvP:  Orcs can't do anything, Humans can't do anything unless the orcs attack a Human NPC.<br />
<br />
Note:  There are quests that require you to kill NPCs on the opposite team, thus turning you PvP.  It is also quite common to raid an enemy city and kill the bankers and quest NPCs (again, turning you PvP).  Even on 'blue' servers you will be PvPing...</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br /><img src="http://www.luclin.org/files/snapdragn/thumbnails/ambear3.jpg" border="0" alt=""></div>
	
	
